351 POUILLY FUISSE; 1957) 3 a a a oe 2 ee 87.05

Good news for those fond of great Pouilly. A small shipment of this, one of the best 1957 Pouilly we have ever tasted, has reached us. From the reputable cellars of one of the deans of Burgundy, Joseph Drouhin.

313 CHABLIS CRU VAULORENT 1958 (due March!) . . . 2.49 27.95

Estate bottled, Domaine Maladiere

Each day the evidence becomes more clear—the 1958 wines of Chablis are entirely delightful and perhaps even better than the 1957. This one, a Premier Cru, is typical in everything that a good Chablis should be.

345 MEURSAULT, CUVEE BAHEZRE DE LANLAY, 1957 . . 4.49 49.75 Acquired at annual auction held at the HOSPICE DE BEAUNE.

At the tasting just prior to the auction, no white wine submitted won the plaudits achieved by this remarkable Meursault. Only 25 cases reached us last month and they soon will be gone. A fabulous, dry, white wine of great depth and magnificent bouquet.
